cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

This paper focuses on generating synthetic imagery for learning visual tasks in urban scenes, specifically object detection in driving scenes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses physically-based augmentation of synthetic imagery, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes an efficient and automatic pipeline, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
